<br>
Now, if Sadaam detonates a nuke against a US invasion, then I would suspect that the US would not reply with nukes... the fallout both literally and figuratively speaking would be too high from neighboring countries.<br>
<br>
The problem with the Mutual Assured Destruction mentallity is that it doesn't work against a terrorist organization that has no home base of operations or does not have a capitol city to destroy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nuclaeon>Nuclaeon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 152<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/17/03 4:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if...Nuclear surprise?</span><hr size=1> If a nation uses such a weapon, then we may have no choice but to completely annihilate the capital city with or without nuclear weapons (i.e. MOAB) else the whole point of deterrence is eliminated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>spacefaring rodent</span><br>  Posts: 1172<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/17/03 8:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if...Nuclear surprise?</span><hr size=1> Ouch, I hadn't considered what the implications for nuclear deterrence would be if we don't use our nukes when we get nuked.  That might send the message to potential adversaries that it's ok to use nukes because we won't necessarily reply in kind.  I think the only certainty from a nuclear strike is the feeding frenzy we'll see from the conspiranuts.  It would definately usher in a new age of fear and probably the death of nuclear energy for peaceful purposes, perhaps even for propulsion use.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :balling --><img src=http://www.smilies-world.de/Smilies/Smilies_klein_1/crying.gif ALT=":balling"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nebobgrenville>nebobgrenville</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://my.oregonstate.edu/courses/1/NE_114_X001_F2002/uploads/homepage/_1060577_1/triga.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 294<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/18/03 6:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if...Nuclear surprise?</span><hr size=1> In order to keep your deterant being useful at all, you almost have to reply with nukes on their military sites, nuking their civilians is probably over the top. Either way things get ugly. There is no way to comw out a winner. <p>&quot;If,&quot; he wispered, &quot;if we could only pick that lock....&quot; - , THE WORLD SET FREE</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sovin>Sovin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tachyon Wrangler</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/18/03 7:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.whitetoweronline.com/hall/images/offedge.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if...Nuclear surprise?</span><hr size=1> Anyone have any info on these &quot;EMP Bombs&quot; I've, once or twice, read about in the news..?  Like loss-of-life/collateral-damage projections as compared to their stated electronics-disrupting usage..?<br>
